    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="889"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d889">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> Files</note>
                <head>No. 889<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States Delegation Working Paper</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d889fn1">Authorship not indicated.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31">July 31,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British proposal<note n="2" xml:id="d889fn2">
                        <ref target="#d888">document No. 888</ref>.</note> regarding imports as a
                    first charge as [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] against exports could well be
                    incorporated by adding the language they propose as a last sentence to Section
                        14–(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) of the Economic Principles. It would then read
                    as follows. (The British language to be added which we agree to with the
                    exception of the word “approved” is underlined).<note n="3" xml:id="d889fn3"
                        >Words underlined in the original document are here italicized.</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“14. Allied controls shall be imposed upon the German economy but only to the
                        extent necessary: <list>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                            <item>…<note n="4" xml:id="d889fn4">Ellipsis in the original.</note>
                            </item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                            <item>to assure the production and maintenance of goods and services
                                required to meet the needs of the occupying forces and displaced
                                persons in Germany and essential to maintain in Germany average
                                living standards not exceeding the average of the standards of
                                living of European countries. (European countries means all European
                                countries excluding U. K. and U. S. S. R.). <hi rend="italic"
                                    >Payment for <del rend="strikethrough">approved</del> imports
                                    into Germany shall be a first charge against the proceeds of
                                    exports out of current production and out of stocks of
                                    goods”</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </p>
                </quote>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
